# Recurring Task Execution Rules

Patch Chain:
- oc-2026.5.20-p002

## Execution Mode Rule

This task is a recurring scheduled job.

The scheduler entry persists between executions.

Each execution MUST create a NEW task sequence number.

Never overwrite previous runs.

Never reuse old task IDs.

Every scheduled execution is treated as a new task run.

## Workspace Execution Rule

Recurring jobs MUST execute as proper OpenClaw workspace tasks inside:

~/.openclaw/workspace/agents/agent1-workspace/

Each recurring run MUST create:

- tasks/task-YYYY-MM-DD-###.md
- planning/plan-YYYY-MM-DD-###.md
- logs/log-YYYY-MM-DD-###.md
- events/event-YYYY-MM-DD-###.json
- results/result-YYYY-MM-DD-###.md
- feedback/feedback-YYYY-MM-DD-###.md

Use the next available same-day sequence number.

The result file MUST contain the embedded final output.

The event file MUST be valid JSON.

The status.json file MUST be updated correctly during the run and finalized only after all required artifacts exist.

## Session Target Rule

Recurring jobs intended for Mission Control artifact history MUST NOT use ephemeral isolated sessions.

Use a persistent named session or workspace-bound session target so the run can write to:

~/.openclaw/workspace/agents/agent1-workspace/

Recommended default:

session:agent1-recurring

A job-specific named session is allowed when useful, for example:

session:tiktok-viral-report

## Delivery Rule

Delivery is best-effort notification behavior.

Delivery failure is NOT task failure.

Task success is determined by workspace artifact creation and structural consistency.

If delivery fails or the delivery channel is unsupported, create a warning in the feedback file and still complete the workspace artifacts.

## Final Output Rule

At the end of each recurring execution, report:

- files created
- files updated
- paths touched
- any remaining structural issues

Do not claim success until all required artifacts exist.
